    "recap_headline": "Marshall University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "Buy Tickets Here\n|\nBox Score (PDF)\n|\nChampionship Fund\nSTATESBORO, Ga. \u2013\nThe Marshall University Baseball team (13-9, 5-1 SBC) suffered its first Sun Belt Conference loss in 2026, 18-12, in its series finale at Georgia Southern on Sunday afternoon.\n\"Today wasn't our day. We have to pitch the ball better than we did today in order to win - 15 free passes is way too many to win good baseball games,\" Herd Baseball Head Coach\nGreg Beals\nsaid. \"All of their ground balls found holes today and when you combine that with free runners, it is a prescription for giving up runs.\u00a0Offensively, I see our approach continue to grow which is encouraging.\u00a0We will ride this bus home and get ready for WVU on Tuesday at The Jack.\"\nAJ Havrilla\nhad a 3-for-5 day at the plate with his second and third homers of the season and four RBI.\nJackson Golden\nhit his first homer in 2026 and drove in three RBI.\nThe Herd got on the board first with a Golden two-RBI single in the second and a solo homer from Havrilla in the third to go up 3-0.\nIn the sixth, Marshall tallied seven runs on RBI singles from\nCleary Simpson\n,\nTyler Kamerer\nand\nEvan Bottone\n, a Golden sacrifice bunt with an error and a Havrilla three-run homer. The seven-run frame put MU back on top 10-6 after GS tallied six runs from the third to fifth innings.\nThe Eagles regained the lead with six runs in the sixth, two in the seventh and four insurance runs in the eighth.\nThe Herd had\nCooper Hinson\ndrive in a run on a sacrifice fly in the top of the eighth and Golden hit a solo homer in the ninth, but the visitors couldn't rally back from the deficit.\nUP NEXT\nThe Herd returns to Jack Cook Field for a five-game homestand starting with in-state rival No. 20 West Virginia on Tuesday night.\nTo donate to the Championship Fund for Marshall baseball, please click\nHERE\n. All proceeds go directly to the Marshall baseball team.\nPar Mar is the presenting sponsor of the 2026 Marshall baseball team. Par Mar is the official convenience store of Marshall Athletics.\nFor all the latest information about Marshall baseball, follow @herdbaseball on Twitter and Instagram.\nTo follow all Thundering Herd sports and get live stats, schedules and free live audio, download the Marshall Athletics App for iOS and Android.\n---HerdZone.com---",
